Reasoning: The paper deals with the decidability of growth-rate properties of imperative programs, which falls under the category of logic (cs.LO). The use of proof rules and the complexity analysis suggest that the paper may also belong to the programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS) categories. The mention of PSPACE-completeness indicates a possible connection to computational complexity (cs.CC), while the shift in focus from proving to disproving suggests a connection to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
